&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;MID ESSEX HOSPITAL SERVICES NHS TRUST&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BROOMFIELD HOSPITAL&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Trust ST1/2 in General/Elderly Care Medicine&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;£31,217 to £41,300 per annum pro rata&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mid Essex Hospitals NHS trust is looking for enthusiastic applicants for the post of Trust Clinical Fellow in Elderly Care Medicine.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a post is to join a dynamic 10 consultant team with 2 Physicians Associates. The Elderly Care Service consists of 4 Care of Elderly wards plus a 7 day Consultant led Frailty Unit with 16 beds and 4 ambulatory trolleys.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This job offers excellent opportunities to work innovatively within a highly motivated team with excellent support for your development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All posts offer candidates experience in General/Elderly medicine and exposure to Specialities within medicine at different levels [ Hospital, Community and an Intermediate setting]. Candidates will also be able to contribute to the acute medical take at a SHO level. We are happy to accommodate any extra/additional speciality experience required by the candidate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Chelmsford offers the combined benefit of a pleasant historic town and a vibrant city, excellent schools and is within about 30 minutes of London by train, with Stansted/Southend airports within 30 minutes by road. With a new Medical School at Anglia Ruskin university at our doorstep.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;yoganathan.suthahar@meht.nhs.uk telephone 01245 514670&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;james.orpin@meht.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
